:
</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[456,491,1965,1992]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[545,582,1965,1991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411" type="female">4♀</specimenCount>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[594,749,1965,1991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">
<collectingCountry box="[594,749,1965,1991]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">SRI LANKA</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, no more locality data given (
<collectionCode box="[1084,1192,1965,1991]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">OUMNH</collectionCode>
b1239, examined). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,2001,2027]" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1886" box="[616,773,2001,2027]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Talaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulifer">
<emphasis box="[616,773,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="411">T. triangulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished by the shorter, broad-based E and the
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">
<collectionCode box="[151,205,151,177]" country="France" name="Jardin Botanique de la Villa Thuret" pageId="7" pageNumber="412" type="Herbarium">VTA</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[263,314,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">RTA</collectionCode>
which are equal in length. Females may be distinguished from congeners by the oval S, relatively longer C shaped CD (
<figureCitation box="[394,521,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[172,1411,188,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-24@8.[165,1423,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6 A–D. Talaus opportunus syntype from Sri Lanka (OUMNH b1239). A left palp, ventral; B same, retrolateral; C epigynum, ventral; D) vulva, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.2 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Figs 6C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
