<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="412" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1487,1874]" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1487,1513]" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,418,1487,1513]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Male:</emphasis>
Prosoma reddish brown, with some long setae, surface with markings. ALE, PLE on tubercles, not connected to each other. ALE&gt;PLE&gt;AME&gt;PME, MOA wider than long, distance between AMEs one diameter of AME. Distance between PME more than 4x AME. Palp: Tibia with VTA large, apically hook-shaped; RTA digitiform and well sclerotised. Bulb kidney-shaped, embolus broad-based, stout, apically pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1263,1333,1595,1622]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[172,1411,188,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-24@8.[165,1423,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6 A–D. Talaus opportunus syntype from Sri Lanka (OUMNH b1239). A left palp, ventral; B same, retrolateral; C epigynum, ventral; D) vulva, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.2 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Figs 6</figureCitation>
A–B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1487,1874]" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">
<emphasis box="[199,292,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Female:</emphasis>
In general, similar to male except for slightly lighter colour, dark spots of the opisthosoma (
<figureCitation box="[1358,1422,1631,1658]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[167,1422,671,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[158,1429,664,1848]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7 A, B. Talaus triangulifer (RMNH.ARA.17832). A right palp (flipped horizontally), ventral; B same, retrolateral. Scale lines = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412534" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412534/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Fig 7</figureCitation>
). Epigynum and vulva as in 
<figureCitation box="[451,520,1667,1693]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[172,1411,188,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-24@8.[165,1423,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6 A–D. Talaus opportunus syntype from Sri Lanka (OUMNH b1239). A left palp, ventral; B same, retrolateral; C epigynum, ventral; D) vulva, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.2 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412532/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="412">Figs 6</figureCitation>
C–D.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
